The following editorial appeared in Monday's Washington Post : With their slick Web sites, pseudo-academic conferences and savvy public relations, the proponents of ``intelligent design'' -- a ``theory'' that challenges the validity of Darwinian evolution -- are far more sophisticated than the creationists of yore. Nevertheless, this new generation of anti-evolutionists, arguing that children have a ``right to question'' scientific truths, has had widespread success in undermining evolutionary theory. Last week, in Pennsylvania's Dover School District, an administrator read a statement to ninth-grade biology students saying that evolution is not fact. 